### Javascript
#### [MODIFY] [index.js](file:///Users/2b/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-brian.rio11@gmail.com/My%20Drive/%F0%9F%94%B5/01%20Grad%20School/02%20SP26/03%20It%27s%20Shader%20Time/W8%20-%20GPU%20Computing/src/index.js)
- **Depth Calculation**: In the [tick()](file:///Users/2b/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-brian.rio11@gmail.com/My%20Drive/%F0%9F%94%B5/01%20Grad%20School/02%20SP26/03%20It%27s%20Shader%20Time/W8%20-%20GPU%20Computing/src/index.js#124-151) animation loop, we need to calculate the camera's depth. Since the camera starts at `y=0` (or `z=5`) and "navigates downward", I will map the camera's vertical position (`-camera.position.y`) to the realistic 0-1000 range. For example: `let depth = Math.max(0, -camera.position.y * 50);`. (We can adjust the `50` multiplier based on how fast you want the descent to feel).
- **Update DOM**: Update `document.getElementById("depth-counter").innerText = \`Depth: ${Math.floor(depth)} ft\`;` in the [tick](file:///Users/2b/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-brian.rio11@gmail.com/My%20Drive/%F0%9F%94%B5/01%20Grad%20School/02%20SP26/03%20It%27s%20Shader%20Time/W8%20-%20GPU%20Computing/src/index.js#124-151) loop. 
- **Interaction Constraint**: Update the `mousedown` event listener. 
  - Add an early return if `event.metaKey` is true (which corresponds to the `Cmd` key on macOS), preventing the flash.
  - Read the currently calculated `depth`. If `depth < 600` or `depth > 800`, do not update `lastClickTime`. This effectively disables the bioluminescence outside of the "Midnight Zone".

## Verification
- Load `http://localhost:8000`.
- Verify the depth counter appears in the bottom right corner at `0 ft`.
- Hold Right-Click (or Shift+Left Click) to Pan the OrbitControls camera downwards. Watch the depth counter increase.
- While depth is `< 600`, click the screen. Verify nothing flashes.
- Pan down until depth is `650`. Click the screen. Verify the screen flashes white and the bioluminescent particles appear.
- Hold `Cmd` and click. Verify that it DOES NOT flash.
